body:
I think maybe I've narrowed it down to the discord streamkit overlay on this end. Methodically removed each source one by one, reading OBS a few times to be sure. One the streamkit overlay was removed and everything else left alone it was fine.

I also have some custom CSS in that streamkit overlay too (basically the common tutorial code for doing fancy avatar popups on screen):

````
li.voice-state:not([data-reactid*="160922867494682625"]) { display:none; }
.avatar {
content:url(https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/813231242362880020/909612208328159282/breadnon_inact.png);
  height:auto !important;
  width:auto !important;
  border-radius:0% !important;
  filter: brightness(50%); 
/*Change brightness to 100%, if you donâ€™t want the image to dim*/
}

.speaking {
  border-color:rgba(0,0,0,0) !important;
  position:relative;
  animation-name: speak-now;
  animation-duration: 1s;
  animation-fill-mode:forwards;
  filter: brightness(100%);
content:url(https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/813231242362880020/909612211062833202/breadnon_act.png);
}

@keyframes speak-now {
  0% { bottom:0px;  }
  15% { bottom:10px;  }
  30% { bottom:0px;  }
}

li.voice-state{ position: static; }
div.user{ position: absolute; left:40%; bottom:5%; }

body { background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); margin: 0px auto; overflow: hidden; }
````
